## Why this dataset

Most public AI Act datasets are either the raw OJ text dump or noisy PDF
scrapes. This one is built from the **official Formex XML** via the
Publications Office Cellar, preserving the regulation's hierarchical
structure (Title → Chapter → Section → Article → Paragraph → Point;
Recitals; Annexes), and adds three pieces of metadata that are tedious
to derive correctly but valuable downstream:

1. **Structural identifiers** on every row — `article_no`, `paragraph_no`,
   `recital_no`, `annex_no`, `annex_section`, plus `references_articles`
   and `interprets_articles` (recitals → the articles they explain).
2. **`effective_from`**, mapped per Article 113 of the AI Act:
   - Articles 1–5 → **2025-02-02** (general provisions + prohibited practices)
   - Chapters V (GPAI), VII (Governance), Articles 28–39, 78, 99–100 → **2025-08-02**
   - Default → **2026-08-02**
   - Article 6(1) → **2027-08-02** (high-risk classification for Annex I products)
3. **Language-invariant `structure_path`**, so an EN row and a NL row covering
   the same provision share the same `structure_path` (e.g. `art:9/par:2`).
   This makes the multilingual rows a parallel corpus by construction.

## How it was built

Pipeline is published as MIT-licensed source code in this repo's companion
GitHub repository. The build is reproducible:

    uv sync
    uv run eu-ai-act-dataset build --output dist --lang en --lang nl --lang fr

Each row carries a `bundle_sha256` (sha of the upstream Formex zip) and a
`snapshot_version` tag so older versions can be reproduced. A weekly GitHub
Action checks for upstream changes and republishes when the source moves.

## Schema

| Column                | Type           | Description                                                  |
|-----------------------|----------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| `id`                  | string         | `art-9-par-2-en`, `rec-102-fr`, `anx-III-sec-4-nl`           |
| `language`            | string         | ISO-639-1: `en`, `nl`, `fr`, ...                             |
| `text`                | string         | Chunk body                                                   |
| `chunk_type`          | string         | `paragraph`, `article_full`, `recital`, `annex_item`         |
| `citation_label`      | string         | `Art. 9(2) AI Act` / `Recital (102) AI Act` / `Annex III, point 4 AI Act` |
| `structure_path`      | string         | Language-invariant key, e.g. `art:9/par:2`                   |
| `title_no`            | int32?         | Title number (Roman numeral → int)                            |
| `chapter_no`          | int32?         | Chapter                                                       |
| `section_no`          | int32?         | Section within a chapter                                      |
| `article_no`          | int32?         | 1–113 for the AI Act                                          |
| `paragraph_no`        | int32?         | Numbered paragraph within an article                          |
| `recital_no`          | int32?         | 1–180 for the AI Act                                          |
| `annex_no`            | string?        | `I`, `II`, …, `XIII` (Roman as written)                       |
| `annex_section`       | string?        | Numbered area within the annex (e.g. `4` for Annex III)       |
| `references_articles` | list<int32>    | Articles this chunk cites in its text                         |
| `interprets_articles` | list<int32>    | Recitals only: articles they interpret                        |
| `defined_terms`       | list<string>   | Article 3 terms appearing verbatim in this chunk              |
| `effective_from`      | date32         | Applicability date per Article 113                            |
| `transitional`        | bool           | True for Article 111 transitional provisions                  |
| `document_id`         | string         | `reg_2024_1689`                                               |
| `celex`               | string         | `{{ celex }}`                                                 |
| `source_url`          | string         | EUR-Lex ELI/OJ URL                                            |
| `source_publisher`    | string         | `European Union`                                              |
| `license`             | string         | `CC BY 4.0`                                                   |
| `snapshot_version`    | string         | This snapshot's version tag (e.g. `v2024-10-17`)              |
| `bundle_sha256`       | string         | sha256 of the upstream Formex bundle (per-language)           |
| `retrieved_at`        | date32         | Build date                                                    |
| `parent_structure_path` | string?      | For `paragraph` chunks: points at the `article_full` parent   |

